{"article_id":"BHlqRJoiYLtB4Phb","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Former federal prosecutor Lori Lightfoot easily won the Chicago mayor 's race Tuesday ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"earning support from every part of the city","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"to defeat a longtime political insider","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"and become the first black woman and openly gay person","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"to lead the nation 's third-largest city .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Lightfoot ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"who had never been elected to public office ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"delivered a commanding victory over Toni Preckwinkle ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"who served in the City Council for 19 years","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"before becoming Cook County Board president .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Preckwinkle also is chairwoman of the county Democratic Party .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"Lightfoot promised to rid City Hall of corruption and help low-income and working-class people","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"she said","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"had been `` left behind and ignored '' by Chicago 's political ruling class .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"It was a message","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"that resonated with voters","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"weary of political scandal and insider deals ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"and who said","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"the city 's leaders for too long have invested in downtown at the expense of neighborhoods .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"`` Together we can and will make Chicago a place","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"where your zip code does n't determine your destiny , ''","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Lightfoot told a cheering crowd at her victory party .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"`` We can and we will break this city 's endless cycle of corruption","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"and never again","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"- never ever -","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"allow politicians to profit from elected positions . ''","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"She said","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"people are seeing `` a city reborn '' -","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"a place","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"where race and `` who you love '' do n't matter .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Lightfoot had emerged as the surprising leader in the first round of voting in February","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"when 14 candidates were on the ballot","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"to succeed Mayor Rahm Emanuel ,","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"who decided against running for a third term .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Chicago will become the largest U.S. city","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"to elect a black woman as mayor","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"when Lightfoot is sworn in May 20 .","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"She will join seven other black women","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"currently serving as mayors in major U.S. cities ,","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"including Atlanta and New Orleans .","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"The vote","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"to succeed Emanuel","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"came just days after Chicago state prosecutors stunned the nation","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"by opting to drop charges against actor Jussie Smollett ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"who was accused of faking a hate-crime attack","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"that implicated supporters of President Trump .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Prosecutors have said","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"they did not intend to vindicate Smollett ,","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"but the actor publicly claimed exoneration","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"-- leading comedians to mock him , and police unions and the mayor 's office to cry foul .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"Lightfoot seized on outrage over the deadly shooting of black teenager Laquan McDonald","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"-- at the hands of white officer Jason Van Dyke --","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"to launch her campaign .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"That was even before Emanuel announced","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"he would n't seek a third term amid criticism","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"for initially resisting calls","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"to release video of the shooting .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"WHY WAS OBAMA CHIEF OF STAFF REACHING OUT TO SMOLLETT PROSECUTOR ?","depth":3},{"id":58,"text":"`` I 'm not a person","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"who decided","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"I would climb the ladder of a corrupt political party , ''","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Lightfoot said during a debate last month .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"`` I do n't hold the title of committeeman , central committeeman , boss of the party . ''","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"That was a not-so-veiled reference to Preckwinkle ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"who also leads the county 's Democratic Party","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"and had countered","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"that her opponent lacked the necessary experience for the job .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"`` This is not an entry-level job , ''","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"Preckwinkle said repeatedly during the campaign .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"`` It 's easy to talk about change .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"It 's hard to actually do it .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"And that 's been my experience","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"- being a change maker , a change agent ,","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"transforming institutions and communities . ''","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"Joyce Ross , 64 , a certified nursing assistant","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"living on the West Side ,","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"said","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"she cast her ballot Tuesday for Lightfoot .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"Ross also said","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"she believed","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Lightfoot would be better able to clean up the police department","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"and curb the city 's violence .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"DRIVE-BY SHOOTING SULLIES MOOD IN CHICAGO , AFTER RELATIVELY GOOD MONTH OF ONLY 20 HOMICIDES","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"In addition , she said","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"she was bothered by Preckwinkle 's association with longtime Alderman Ed Burke ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"who was indicted earlier this year on charges","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"he tried to shake down a restaurant owner","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"who wanted to build in his ward .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"`` My momma always said","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"birds of a feather flock together , ''","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"Ross said .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"The campaign between the two women got off to a contentious start ,","depth":4},{"id":92,"text":"with Preckwinkle 's advertising focusing on Lightfoot 's work as a partner at Mayer Brown , one of the nation 's largest law firms ,","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"and tagging her as a `` wealthy corporate lawyer . ''","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"Preckwinkle also tried to cast Lightfoot as an insider","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"for working in police oversight posts under Emanuel and police oversight , procurement and emergency communications posts under former Mayor Richard M. Daley .","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"In one ad , Preckwinkle criticized Lightfoot 's oversight of emergency communications in 2004","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"when a fire killed four children .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"A judge ordered Lightfoot to preserve 911 tapes","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"after questions were raised","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"about how the emergency call was handled .","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"The ad noted","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"some of the tapes were destroyed ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"prompting the judge to rebuke Lightfoot .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"The ad sparked a backlash from the family of three of the children","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"killed ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"with their sister accusing Preckwinkle of trying to take advantage of her family 's tragedy .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"Lightfoot also responded","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"by scolding her opponent","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"for being negative","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"while also airing ads","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"pointing out Preckwinkle 's connection to powerful local Democrats ,","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"including one under federal indictment .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"Preckwinkle spent much of her time during the campaign","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"answering for her ties to Chicago 's political establishment .","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"She and her supporters asserted","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"her rise to Democratic Party leadership did not hinder her ability","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"to oppose policies","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"promoted by the city 's ever-powerful mayors .","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"`` My whole career has been about change ,","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"and change is action and results , not simply words , ''","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"said Preckwinkle ,","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"who said","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"her experience made her better positioned","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"to lead a city with financial problems and poorer neighborhoods","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"hit by gun violence .","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"Despite the barbs on the campaign trail , the two advanced similar ideas","depth":6},{"id":127,"text":"to boost the city 's finances .","depth":6},{"id":128,"text":"Both candidates expressed support for a casino in Chicago and for changing the state 's income tax system to a graduated tax ,","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"in which higher earners would be taxed at a higher rate .","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"Preckwinkle said","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"while downtown development should remain a priority ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"it should not be at the cost of neighborhood growth .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"She promoted additional investments in neighborhood schools , affordable housing and criminal justice reform .","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"Lightfoot said","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"that as mayor , she would focus on investing in neighborhoods on the West and South Sides","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"and bring transparency and accountability to City Hall .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"She added","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"she also wanted to end City Hall corruption","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"and restore people 's faith in government .","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"`` The machine 's been in decline for a while ,","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"but it still has a grip on certain things , ''","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"Lightfoot said .","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"`` This is our opportunity","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"to send it to its grave , once and for all . ''","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":291,"left":202,"right":290,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":175,"right":201,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":156,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":150,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":147,"right":149,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":2,"right":148,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":148,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":151,"right":154,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":151,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":7,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":152,"right":10,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},